\u0432 \u0437\u0430\u043b\u043e\u0436\u043d\u0438\u043a\u0438 \u043e\u043b\u0438\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0445\u0430]</ref><ref>[https://www.kinoafisha.info/movies/8330091/ \u0417\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434, 2017]</ref> It was selected to be screened in the Contemporary World Cinema section at the [[2018 Toronto International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"TIFF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/08/tiff-2018-additional-titles-mid90s-boy-erased-hold-the-dark-1201993789/ |title=TIFF Adds More High-Profile Titles, Including Jonah Hill\u2019s \u2018Mid90s,\u2019 \u2018Boy Erased,\u2019 \u2018Hold the Dark,\u2019 and Many More |work=IndieWire |accessdate=24 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe owner of the Kalugin's factory informed the workers that he will be  obliged to close it soon as it is not profitable.  The boss, a local [[Russian oligarch|oligarch]] called Kalugin was kidnapped from his car by masked and armed persons who demanded for him a big ransom. The money is taken to the workers by the head of the oligarch personal security team. His heavily armed mercenaries arrive at night at the factory where the boss is being held hostage.\n\nThose who barricaded themselves in the workshop are local workers led by a former [[Spetsnaz|Special Forces]] soldier, nicknamed Sedoi. Six months without a salary and the impending bankruptcy of the plant pushed them to a desperate step.\n\nTo pull out their boss, nothing will stop the mercenaries. But unlike them, hard workers have nothing more to lose.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Denis Shvedov]] as Sedoi\n* [[Andrey Smolyakov]] as Konstantin Kalugin\n* [[Vladislav Abashin]] as Tuman\n* [[Ivan Yankovsky]] as Vladimir\n* [[Aleksandr Bukharov (actor)|Aleksandr Bukharov]] as Terekhov\n* [[Dmitri Kulichkov]] as Ryaboi<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt5966602/fullcredits/?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm \u0417\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434 (2018) Full Cast & Crew ]</ref>\n* [[Kirill Polukhin]] as Andreich\n*Yuriy Tarasov as  \u00abVesyolyiy\u00bb\n*Aleksey Komashko as \u00abSedmoy\u00bb\n*Aleksey Faddeev as \u00abPonomar\u00bb\n\n==Production==\nThe filming began on October 2017.<ref>[https://tvkinoradio.ru/news/new12273-yurij-bikov-nachal-semki-filma-zavod \u042e\u0440\u0438\u0439 \u0411\u044b\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u043d\u0430\u0447\u0430\u043b \u0441\u044a\u0435\u043c\u043a\u0438 \u0444\u0438\u043b\u044c\u043c\u0430 \u00ab\u0417\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u00bb]</ref>  The shooting took place at a real factory of reinforced concrete structures in the Sokolniki district (Moscow), the work of the plant was not stopped during the shooting.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}} Official selection of the Beaune (France) 11th Festival international du film policier.\n\n== External links ==\n* {{official |https://www.wildbunch.biz/movie/the-factory/}}\n* {{IMDb title|5966602}}\n* [https://www.kinopoisk.ru/article/3260011/ \u00ab\u041f\u0440\u044f\u043c\u043e\u043b\u0438\u043d\u0435\u0439\u043d\u043e\u00bb: \u0418\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043d\u043d\u0430\u044f \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0441\u0441\u0430 \u043e \u00ab\u0417\u0430\u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435\u00bb \u0411\u044b\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0430]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Factory, The}}\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:Russian-language films]]\n[[Category:Russian films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Armenian films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Yuri Bykov]]\n[[Category:Films about kidnapping]]\n[[Category:Fictional factory workers]]\n[[Category:Films about social issues]]<!-- per www.tiff.net/tiff/the-factory/ -->\n[[Category:Films about labour]]\n[[Category:Films about labor relations]]\n[[Category:2010s crime thriller films]]\n[[Category:Russian crime films]]\n[[Category:Russian thriller films]]\n", "name_user": "Vilnyy", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eProduction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Factory_(2018_film)"}
